<subSubSection pageId="13" pageNumber="35" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1437,1721,2033]" pageId="13" pageNumber="35">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,333,1865,1889]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="35" reason="1">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific epithet is a noun in apposition and refers to the bump present on the RTA of the male palp.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="13" pageNumber="35" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1437,1721,2033]" pageId="13" pageNumber="35">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,321,1937,1962]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="35" reason="1">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Males of this species are similar to those of 
<taxonomicName authority="Ruiz, 2011" authorityName="Ruiz" authorityYear="2011" box="[856,969,1937,1961]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Soesilarishius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="13" pageNumber="35" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="albipes" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[856,969,1937,1961]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="35">S. albipes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[979,1072,1937,1961]" pageId="13" pageNumber="35">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[979,1072,1937,1961]" pageId="13" pageNumber="35" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
for having light front legs and straight emboli in the palp (see 
<figureCitation box="[507,636,1973,1997]" captionStart="FIGURES 34–38" captionStartId="11.[151,263,1723,1746]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,591,1699]" captionTargetId="figure-353@11.[151,1436,591,1699]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 34–38. Soesilarishius spinipes sp. nov. 34 male habitus (paratype IBSP 160766); 35 female habitus (paratype IBSP 160763). Soesilarishius albipes sp. nov. 36 male habitus (paratype IBSP 160817); 37 female habitus (paratype IBSP 160812). Soesilarishius dromedarius sp. nov. 38 male habitus (paratype IBSP 160856)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5280716" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5280716/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="35">Figs 36, 38</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[648,722,1973,1997]" captionStart="FIGURES 39–44" captionStartId="13.[151,263,1491,1514]" captionTargetBox="[172,1422,395,1471]" captionTargetId="figure-232@13.[151,1436,375,1477]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURES 39–44. Soesilarishius albipes sp. nov. 39–40 left male palp (39 ventral, 40 retrolateral); 41 epigyne, ventral view; 42 vulva, dorsal view. Soesilarishius dromedarius sp. nov. 43–44 left male palp (43 ventral, 44 retrolateral)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5280718" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5280718/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="35">39, 43</figureCitation>
), but can be easily distinguished by having a bump on the RTA (
<figureCitation box="[159,244,2009,2033]" captionStart="FIGURES 39–44" captionStartId="13.[151,263,1491,1514]" captionTargetBox="[172,1422,395,1471]" captionTargetId="figure-232@13.[151,1436,375,1477]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURES 39–44. Soesilarishius albipes sp. nov. 39–40 left male palp (39 ventral, 40 retrolateral); 41 epigyne, ventral view; 42 vulva, dorsal view. Soesilarishius dromedarius sp. nov. 43–44 left male palp (43 ventral, 44 retrolateral)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5280718" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5280718/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="35">Fig. 44</figureCitation>
). Females are unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
